<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Sweet-and-twenty" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Sweet-and-twenty,</orth> a term of endearment: <cit><quote>then come kiss me, s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 2.3.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 3, 52</bibl></cit> (cf. <cit><quote>good even and twenty, good Master Page!</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.202" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 202</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>tricks eleven and twenty long,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 2, 57</bibl></cit>).
